reviews.review_text:
I love the look of these frames -- they are exactly what I wanted. I was very excited about finally ordering new glasses from WP.  
The information online was helpful in selecting the correct size, and they fit very well. Try at home didn't seem to be an option, but I wanted to get them ordered anyway, so I didn't try them on first. The website did recommend a wide size for me, but I went by the numbers on my existing frames and ordered the regular fit instead. reviews.title: Stylish and Comfortable: A Winning Combination fro
reviews.review_text:
I recently purchased a pair of Warby Parker glasses, and I couldn't be happier with my decision. From the moment I opened the sleek and eco-friendly packaging, I knew I was in for a treat. Warby Parker's attention to detail and commitment to quality were evident right from the start.

First and foremost, the style of the glasses is impeccable. The design is modern and chic, striking the perfect balance between trendy and timeless. The wide range of frame options available made it easy for me to find a pair that suits my personal style, and the virtual try-on feature on their website was incredibly helpful in making my decision.

Beyond the stylish appearance, the glasses are exceptionally comfortable to wear. The lightweight frames sit comfortably on my face, and the high-quality materials used ensure durability without compromising on comfort. The attention to ergonomics is evident, making these glasses ideal for extended wear without any discomfort.

The prescription lenses are spot on, providing crystal-clear vision with no distortions. I appreciate the anti-reflective coating, which reduces glare and enhances visual clarity, especially when using digital devices. The overall craftsmanship of the glasses reflects Warby Parker's commitment to delivering a top-notch product.

What sets Warby Parker apart is their socially conscious business model. For every pair of glasses sold, they donate a pair to someone in need, making it a brand that not only cares about its customers but also about making a positive impact on the world. Knowing that my purchase contributes to a greater cause adds an extra layer of satisfaction.

In conclusion, my experience with Warby Parker has been nothing short of fantastic. From the stylish design and comfort to the precision of the lenses and the company's commitment to social responsibility, I can confidently say that these glasses are a winning combination. I wholeheartedly recommend Warby Parker to anyone in search of quality eyewear with a touch of style and a socially conscious ethos.

reviews.review_text:
I've a very large head and the Brady frame fits nicely and looks fine.  The reason for the low star rating in the readers lens.  The lens of the first pair had an unnatural yellow-green tint; I called Warby and they sent a replacement.    The replacement also has the yellow-green tint.  If you hold the glasses infront of you with one hand - and another pair in the other hand ... the tinting is obvious.

The tinting isnt a big deal in everyday situations like reading, working on a computer etc - but I do a good deal of photography image editing - and I have to take the Brady off and put on another pair that has a clear lens.   Because of this I dont recommend the Brady with a lens from Warby.   The frame is nice - but the lens, nope.

I've a very large head and the Brady frame fits nicely and looks fine.  The reason for the low star rating in the readers lens.  The lens of the first pair had an unnatural yellow-green tint; I called Warby and they sent a replacement.    The replacement also has the yellow-green tint.  If you hold the glasses infront of you with one hand - and another pair in the other hand ... the tinting is obvious.

The tinting isnt a big deal in everyday situations like reading, working on a computer etc - but I do a good deal of photography image editing - and I have to take the Brady off and put on another pair that has a clear lens. I don't know why, but I just love the idea of WP. My wife and I were at the mall one day and there was an actual Warby Parker store there, so I popped in (with our two young kids!) and tried on some glasses.

The store employees were so great!  They let my young daughters try on glasses (as they were running around the store).  They were super helpful for me too -- directing me to the type of frames I wanted.

All in all I found my glasses super quickly and paid for them right there.  I subsequently went to get my eyes checked at a different place and sent in the Rx for my eyes.  My insurance (VSP) even covered $70 of the $95 price!

reviews.review_text: The frame was the only one I tried on ~ and I love it! reviews.title: Enjoying my new WPs!
reviews.review_text: This are my second pair or Warby Parkers. I love the fun color and frame. The quality is nice and I appreciate the price. My glasses arrived sooner than expected.  Overall a great experience!

reviews.title: Perfect first pair of glasses!
reviews.review_text: I am a first time eyeglass wearer and purchaser - I loved the WP try on options. It helped me find my perfect fit! I picked two pair - the Ira and the Daisy frames. The purple quartz pattern on the Daisy is beautiful! I get so many compliments on them. They fit well and are comfortable to wear when reading, studying, crafting, etc.

reviews.title: Awesome Glasses

reviews.review_text: I bought my frames from Warby Parker a few years ago and I love them so much that I had my new prescription lenses replaced in the same frames! The staff were very friendly and helpful. I received my glasses in the mail in good time. The whole process is very easy!

reviews.title: Compliments
reviews.review_text: This is not my first purchase from Warby Parker and I continue to be impressed. My granddaughter is also a repeat customer. They carry a very narrow line that works so well for me and keeps me returning. Only comment, is that I would like to see more color options in this line. The glasses are high quality and reasonably priced and the encounters with the staff have been helpful, professional and positive.

reviews.title: Absolutely love!
reviews.review_text: I am typically a contacts wearer because every time I get glasses they always bothered me when wearing them. I would feel off balance or my depth perception was off! Now Iâ€™m talking over 30 years of never being comfortable wearing my glasses. Well that has all changed with my Warby Parker Daisy glasses.  I LOVE THEM!  I wore them shopping, doing housework, and hiking in the woods and never felt off balance or irritated by the glasses. The staff in the store were very helpful and when I needed the glasses tweaked a little to fit perfectly, they were quick and courteous. And you canâ€™t beat the price!! And the choice!!  Definitely recommend getting your glasses at Warby Parker!

reviews.title: They have their sights on customer service
reviews.review_text: I've been wearing prescription eyeglasses since I was 12 years old and have never truly loved a pair of glasses like the ones I just purchased from Warby Parker. My friends and family have all complimented me wearing them. Originally, I went to my eye doctor inquiring about their cost of lenses and frames. The prescription alone would have cost me $600 not including frames. I just couldn't justify spending that amount of money. My niece recommended Warby Parker, and there is a store in Wesley Chapel, Florida where I live. I prefer trying on frames in person, so I was very excited. They were so helpful and took the time to select a number of frames that would go well with the shape of my face. My old frames were always a little too wide.  The sales associate at Warby Parker took that into account when helping me select my frames. The store was also very clean and the sample frames were in top shape. Other optical places I visited did not have that personal customer service like Warby Parker and they weren't as clean either. Since sharing my experience and the cost savings with others, two of my friends have decided to visit Warby Parker.

reviews.title: Want to love but....
reviews.review_text:
I really want to give these higher stars, and I know all of my issues may not be WP's fault, so I'm giving a very mid rating. 

The process of the try on before you buy is a very good process! However, please check to see if an actual store store or kiosk is near you. I found this out after I already got my trial pairs. I would have just gone into the store and tried on unlimited frames versus only 5, and been limited to the frames available for home try on, because it is very limited. 

My glasses were done in a decent time frame, but I have had these a month now (past the return window) and I am still experiencing blurriness and eye strain and headaches. I know this may not completely be WP's faultt, and more to do with my prescription. But my prescription barely changed according to my doctor and this is not my first rodeo, being a glasses wearer for more than 20 years, I know what to expect when adjusting to new glasses. 

The frames are beautiful and I really want to like my pair but I'll have to think hard about buying from WB again, honestly. At the very least I'll just go into the actual store next time.

reviews.title: Nice frame shape for a wide face
reviews.review_text: I have a wide face, so sometimes my frame options are pretty limited. I got these in the wider width option. Overall I'm happy with the style and shape of these, this is as close to what I've imagined a round style should look like on my face (everything else I've tried has been too narrow). The arms were too long and needed a lot of adjusting. I like the purple mixed into the tortoiseshell, but unfortunately there is one large purple piece right in the center of the bridge and it looks a little odd to me. The quality seems to be good, though. I had some issues on the customer service side and it took nearly a month before I received my order.

reviews.title: Glasses different than samples
reviews.review_text:
The customer service people I spoke with were amazing, but the glasses that I tried on at home were not exactly the same as the ones I received. Â I ordered them based on the purple the sample ones had, but when I recieved the you could not see any purple when wearing. Â I sent them back & got a new pair, but they were the same, not showing the purple. Given the name was purple magnolia, you would think you would be able to see the purple, but no only the actual prescription pairs ordered you see purple on the inside of the glasses, which is use
useless, as you want the accent on the outer part of glasses.

reviews.title: Less than exciting
reviews.review_text: I had a similar frame/Rx filled about 2 years ago. Unfortunately, while cleaning the glasses they snapped in two right in the nose bridge and were irreparable. I had no choice but to buy a replacement. I was surprised they had not lasted very long. On top of that, when I went to the store the "tech was inexperienced and did not measure correctly the alignment.  So I had to wait twice for them to be made, remade. After all that, they are not quite right and with what I paid I am less than enthusiastic about going down this path again.

reviews.title: Uncommon misstep
reviews.review_text:
My previous experiences with multiple Warby Parker orders were positive. This time, there were a couple of missteps which I found very frustrating, given WPs favorable customer service.
1) I returned my Try-On package to my local store and ordered one of the pairs from the box. The WP associate marked the lenses with the red dots and they submitted the order. A few days later, that very same box, including the sample pair with the red dots, was delivered to my house and I had to once again bring it down to the store. It took a while for the associates to understand what had happened, but eventually they got it.
2) Even though my previous orders said delivery in 7-10 business days, my glasses always arrived earlier than expected. This time, however, my order took 2 weeks (14 business days) to arrive. It was frustrating because I had ordered the glasses in time for a scheduled work trip, but they were delivered late.
I will probably still order from Warby Parker...your associates are always very friendly and professional, and the mix-up with the sample try-ons was not a big deal. I'm hoping that the delayed delivery was a fluke.
Just wanted to give you feedback from a loyal customer.

reviews.title: An Eyeglass Company Like No Other!
reviews.review_text: This was my fifth pair of glasses from Warby Parker and I love them all! However, I really want to compliment the company and customer service. I recently had eye surgery and was given a new prescription, which I promptly took to WP for two new pairs of glasses. As always, they arrived promptly. Imagine my dismay when I was unable to see with them! I returned to my eye doctor to make sure they were made correctly (which they 100% were). Upon receiving a new exam, the doctor determined that the first prescription was in error and wrote a new one. Thinking I was now stuck with $300 worth of glasses I couldn't use, I called Warby Parker to see what could be done. Their reply? "No problem. Just bring in your glasses and new prescription and we will replace the lenses at no cost." Who does that in today's world? I am a Warby Parker fan for life!

reviews.title: Stylish and Comfortable: A Winning Combination fro
reviews.review_text:
I recently purchased a pair of Warby Parker glasses, and I couldn't be happier with my decision. From the moment I opened the sleek and eco-friendly packaging, I knew I was in for a treat. Warby Parker's attention to detail and commitment to quality were evident right from the start.

First and foremost, the style of the glasses is impeccable. The design is modern and chic, striking the perfect balance between trendy and timeless. The wide range of frame options available made it easy for me to find a pair that suits my personal style, and the virtual try-on feature on their website was incredibly helpful in making my decision.

Beyond the stylish appearance, the glasses are exceptionally comfortable to wear. The lightweight frames sit comfortably on my face, and the high-quality materials used ensure durability without compromising on comfort. The attention to ergonomics is evident, making these glasses ideal for extended wear without any discomfort.

The prescription lenses are spot on, providing crystal-clear vision with no distortions. I appreciate the anti-reflective coating, which reduces glare and enhances visual clarity, especially when using digital devices. The overall craftsmanship of the glasses reflects Warby Parker's commitment to delivering a top-notch product.

What sets Warby Parker apart is their socially conscious business model. For every pair of glasses sold, they donate a pair to someone in need, making it a brand that not only cares about its customers but also about making a positive impact on the world. Knowing that my purchase contributes to a greater cause adds an extra layer of satisfaction.

In conclusion, my experience with Warby Parker has been nothing short of fantastic. From the stylish design and comfort to the precision of the lenses and the company's commitment to social responsibility, I can confidently say that these glasses are a winning combination. I wholeheartedly recommend Warby Parker to anyone in search of quality eyewear with a touch of style and a socially conscious ethos.

The lens of the first pair had an unnatural yellow-green tint; I called Warby and they sent a replacement.    The replacement also has the yellow-green tint.  If you hold the glasses infront of you with one hand - and another pair in the other hand ... the tinting is obvious.

The tinting isnt a big deal in everyday situations like reading, working on a computer etc - but I do a good deal of photography image editing - and I have to take the Brady off and put on another pair that has a clear lens.   Because of this I dont recommend the Brady with a lens from Warby.   The frame is nice - but the lens, nope.

The tinting isnt a big deal in everyday situations like reading, working on a computer etc - but I do a good deal of photography image editing - and I have to take the Brady off and put on another pair that has a clear lens.   Because of this I dont recommend the Brady with a lens from Warby.   The frame is nice - but the lens, nope.

reviews.title: Great service and Product!
reviews.review_text:
I bought this frame a few months ago.  I haven't needed glasses for years (I got Lasik in the mid 2000's).  I went to a conference about 6 months ago and found I couldn't read the screen from the back of the room, so I decided to get some specs.

I don't know why, but I just love the idea of WP. My wife and I were at the mall one day and there was an actual Warby Parker store there, so I popped in (with our two young kids!) and tried on some glasses.

The store employees were so great!  They let my young daughters try on glasses (as they were running around the store).  They were super helpful for me too -- directing me to the type of frames I wanted.

All in all I found my glasses super quickly and paid for them right there.  I subsequently went to get my eyes checked at a different place and sent in the Rx for my eyes.  My insurance (VSP) even covered $70 of the $95 price!

reviews.title: They have their sights on customer service
reviews.review_text: I've been wearing prescription eyeglasses since I was 12 years old and have never truly loved a pair of glasses like the ones I just purchased from Warby Parker. My friends and family have all complimented me wearing them. Originally, I went to my eye doctor inquiring about their cost of lenses and frames. The prescription alone would have cost me $600 not including frames. I just couldn't justify spending that amount of money. My niece recommended Warby Parker, and there is a store in Wesley Chapel, Florida where I live. I prefer trying on frames in person, so I was very excited. They were so helpful and took the time to select a number of frames that would go well with the shape of my face. My old frames were always a little too wide.  The sales associate at Warby Parker took that into account when helping me select my frames. The store was also very clean and the sample frames were in top shape. Other optical places I visited did not have that personal customer service like Warby Parker and they weren't as clean either. Since sharing my experience and the cost savings with others, two of my friends have decided to visit Warby Parker.

reviews.title: Want to love but....
reviews.review_text:
I really want to give these higher stars, and I know all of my issues may not be WP's fault, so I'm giving a very mid rating. 

The process of the try on before you buy is a very good process! However, please check to see if an actual store store or kiosk is near you. I found this out after I already got my trial pairs. I would have just gone into the store and tried on unlimited frames versus only 5, and been limited to the frames available for home try on, because it is very limited. 

My glasses were done in a decent time frame, but I have had these a month now (past the return window) and I am still experiencing blurriness and eye strain and headaches. I know this may not completely be WP's faultt, and more to do with my prescription. But my prescription barely changed according to my doctor and this is not my first rodeo, being a glasses wearer for more than 20 years, I know what to expect when adjusting to new glasses. 

The frames are beautiful and I really want to like my pair but I'll have to think hard about buying from WB again, honestly. At the very least I'll just go into the actual store next time.

reviews.review_text: I am very pleased with my purchase - excellent price point and up to date style without breaking the bank. Excellent customer service & marketing tools. Prior to going to the storefront I spent time on line virtually trying on different pairs of glasses as well as trying on at different times of day. This process had me pare down my choices and prevented me from being overwhelmed when I entered the store. reviews.title: Uncommon misstep
reviews.review_text:
My previous experiences with multiple Warby Parker orders were positive. This time, there were a couple of missteps which I found very frustrating, given WPs favorable customer service.
1) I returned my Try-On package to my local store and ordered one of the pairs from the box. The WP associate marked the lenses with the red dots and they submitted the order. A few days later, that very same box, including the sample pair with the red dots, was delivered to my house and I had to once again bring it down to the store. It took a while for the associates to understand what had happened, but eventually they got it.
2) Even though my previous orders said delivery in 7-10 business days, my glasses always arrived earlier than expected. This time, however, my order took 2 weeks (14 business days) to arrive. It was frustrating because I had ordered the glasses in time for a scheduled work trip, but they were delivered late.
I will probably still order from Warby Parker...your associates are always very friendly and professional, and the mix-up with the sample try-ons was not a big deal. I'm hoping that the delayed delivery was a fluke.
Just wanted to give you feedback from a loyal customer.

I then went in to get them adjusted so they wouldn't slide off my face.  The employee simply looked behind my ear and without any input from me, made huge adjustments to them making them very tight.  I did ask him to  readjusted back some, but after more wear, I find they are still too tight and unwearable.  He didn't listen well or ask a single question about how I would want them adjusted.  Now I am frustrated that I have to go back in for a fourth time... Overall, I think it is hit or miss as far as who you are working with in the store. reviews.title: An Eyeglass Company Like No Other!
reviews.review_text: This was my fifth pair of glasses from Warby Parker and I love them all! However, I really want to compliment the company and customer service. I recently had eye surgery and was given a new prescription, which I promptly took to WP for two new pairs of glasses. As always, they arrived promptly. Imagine my dismay when I was unable to see with them! I returned to my eye doctor to make sure they were made correctly (which they 100% were). Upon receiving a new exam, the doctor determined that the first prescription was in error and wrote a new one. Thinking I was now stuck with $300 worth of glasses I couldn't use, I called Warby Parker to see what could be done. Their reply? "No problem. Just bring in your glasses and new prescription and we will replace the lenses at no cost." Who does that in today's world? I am a Warby Parker fan for life!

reviews.title: Excellent Quality Glasses and Service
reviews.review_text:
This is my first experience with online eyeglasses shopping and I love the Warby Parker experience. First of all, choosing lenses was enhanced by virtual try-on, which encouraged and taught me what shapes worked best for my face. Second, the free option to try on five frames at home allowed me to narrow down the choices even further.  Instructions that came with the frames gave me more information on how to judge which ones were best for my face.  I was able to decide between regular lenses in one pair, plus Rx sunglasses, or else clear lenses with transition darkening. I chose the latter.  Then, it was so easy to return the frames. Note, in my town, the USPS carriers wonâ€™t pick up parcels from homes, if they are not scheduled beforehand, but it was easy to drop off at the PO. 
Next step, ordering was easy, because I could send a photo of my prescription that I took with my phone. The order was completed with only one extra step because the PD, pupillary distance, was unclear on the copy of the Rx that I had. I could do that step with my phone, though. I was delighted that they were able to connect with my vision insurance immediately, even though my coverage was so new I didnâ€™t even have my ID card yet. I paid through PayPal, again easy. Finally, communication with them by email and online was clear, swift, easy, and professional. I heard by email each step of the way. Shipping was swift and tracking steps were announced. The glasses arrived safely and work very well. I bought elsewhere some polarized sunglasses that fit over these, because the transition ones darken only before getting in the car, but those other ones work even better over them inside the car glass. Iâ€™m having the best of all options for me this way, rather than separate eyeglasses and Rx sunglasses to carry around.  The glasses look good, as well. Learning to use the new Rx, putting the extra car shades over top didnâ€™t take long to get used to. I can see so well with these that Iâ€™ll use the Warby Parker service gladly in the future and will recommend it highly.

Try at home didn't seem to be an option, but I wanted to get them ordered anyway, so I didn't try them on first. The website did recommend a wide size for me, but I went by the numbers on my existing frames and ordered the regular fit instead. I'm glad that I did, so just know that the numbers may be more reliable than the online recommendations, depending on how you like your frames to fit. I was nervous about the PD measuring process, but it seems to have worked great as well. Overall, I'm pleased with the experience.

My niece recommended Warby Parker, and there is a store in Wesley Chapel, Florida where I live. I prefer trying on frames in person, so I was very excited. They were so helpful and took the time to select a number of frames that would go well with the shape of my face. My old frames were always a little too wide.  The sales associate at Warby Parker took that into account when helping me select my frames. The store was also very clean and the sample frames were in top shape. Other optical places I visited did not have that personal customer service like Warby Parker and they weren't as clean either. Since sharing my experience and the cost savings with others, two of my friends have decided to visit Warby Parker.

reviews.review_text: I've been wearing prescription eyeglasses since I was 12 years old and have never truly loved a pair of glasses like the ones I just purchased from Warby Parker. My friends and family have all complimented me wearing them. Originally, I went to my eye doctor inquiring about their cost of lenses and frames. The prescription alone would have cost me $600 not including frames. I just couldn't justify spending that amount of money. My niece recommended Warby Parker, and there is a store in Wesley Chapel, Florida where I live. I prefer trying on frames in person, so I was very excited. They were so helpful and took the time to select a number of frames that would go well with the shape of my face. My old frames were always a little too wide.  The sales associate at Warby Parker took that into account when helping me select my frames. The store was also very clean and the sample frames were in top shape. Other optical places I visited did not have that personal customer service like Warby Parker and they weren't as clean either. Since sharing my experience and the cost savings with others, two of my friends have decided to visit Warby Parker.

reviews.title: If you need glasses ASAP this sight is not for you
reviews.review_text:
I recently just purchased a pair of glasses. The whole process took f o r e v e r. I picked our five to try on and it took them almost 3 weeks to send them. The day I got them was the same day I chose what I wanted and sent them back. It took almost a month for them to send my glasses. Luckily, I have contacts so I was surviving because it took almost a month to receive my glasses! 

The glasses themselves are nothing special. I had to have my husband tighten them since they were pretty loose. 

The price I paid was the service I received. Cheap.

reviews.title: Disappointed beyond belief
reviews.review_text:
Number of glasses/lens ordered:3
Price of total order ~$501
Number of mistakes in my orders:6
Number of hours to resolve these mistakes:4
Promised in 5 to 7 business days, actual final delivery took about 3 times longer

Your attempts at service recovery were meager and too little too late. At this point it is not about the numbers.  I have been very impressed with Warby Parkers business model of donating a pair for every pair purchased.  I shared that fact with anyone who wondered where to go.  Unfortunately this experience has shown me that your philanthropy is carried on the shoulders of your customers and how you value your customers (and wonder about your employees) lacks the appreciation that they deserve.  For what is a company without its customers?   Regrettably,  I am no longer a customer.

reviews.title: Rude and unaccommodating staff.

Awful experience with these people and trying to get properly made glasses.

reviews.title: Literally non-stop compliments
reviews.review_text: I have a large number of WP frames but I tend to gravitate toward a similar style and color, roundish acetate in torts of varying brown-type colors lol. A few greens in there as well. So, I thought I'd step a little outside my comfort zone and try a bit of a different color and a more pronounced, textural frame with the Javier in Brown Sugar Crystal. While at first I was really unsure of the color as I thought it might not work well with my very pale, ginger complexion and hair but I guess I just have no idea what looks good because every single time I wear them I get multiple compliments on the really interesting look of the frame as well as the color! So, I def recommend them, they really are pretty rad looking with the geometric diamond cuts on the face front and the bold silhouette. Most of my WP frames, as in probably 20 of 23 pairs are a medium fit, however I am a smidge on the narrow end of a medium so this frame which is a smidge on the wider end of medium is one I did need to have a couple of adjustments on to get it fitting just right. Nothing major and it was certainly doable by a WP optician but in case anyone out there with a solidly narrow face is looking at this frame, it will probably just be a little too big and might not be a great option.

reviews.title: Total winner!

reviews.title: Not a great experience overall
reviews.review_text:
OK - background to my purchase. I bought glasses from Warby Parker while I was down in the USA (I live in Canada). A friend of mine had a good experience and said that I could avoid hassle and high costs through this retailer. 
I should also preface that every individual that helped me genuinely tried their best to help me through the process. However, it soon became a comedy of small errors that made the overall experience regretful. 

First off, I ordered two glasses and the shipping department sent one my glasses to a location in the USA - my friend was able to forward them but I was assured at the store that both pairs would reach me in Canada. Second, one of my pairs of glasses was a completely wrong size (wide) when the other pair was correct (medium). Third, when I got the wide pair and got them fitted at a different retailer in Canada, I was told by an optician that the combination of my thick lens and the moulded frame (not metal) was not recommended because even though they could be adjusted by bending the frame, they explained that, over time, the frame would 'bounce back' to its original shape - making them unwearable. 

The shipping experience was bad. I first contacted WP's support to inquire when I was getting into the fourth week without receiving my glasses - I was told it was still within their 'window' for delivery even though the tracking shown that it was in New York as 'processing' for 3 weeks. I had to contact them again when I realized they would not make their window, the second support person I contacted was much more helpful in figuring out that my medium glasses had gone astray in shipping. He corrected the issue by re-issuing my order (which took another 3 weeks to get to me). So, when it came to the wide pair, the glasses were obviously not going to work for me, I contacted support again to see what could be done. Due to the issue of me being in Canada, ordering from the USA, they recommended that I send the wide pair back for a refund. However, the shipping department (or a computer) did not take this into account and they sent me a return label as if I was in the USA (postage paid for the US Postal system). I had to contact them again to get a re-issue for my return label to send through a Canadian carrier.

As I said, the overall impression of Warby Parker was one in which their employees would try to help as best they could but I can honestly say that I won't consider going through them again. Unless, I do it locally (but that is obviously up to the cost they would charge for glasses in Canada - FYI, prescription glasses in Canada are burdensomely expensive compared to other markets). I know that my experience was unique but I sending this on with the hopes that things improve (and urge them to open a store in Calgary, Alberta).

reviews.title: A whole new simple, sophisticated look!
reviews.review_text:
It's been two months since I stepped into the Warby Parker store in New York and walked out with a life-changing pair of glasses: the Abe frames. Since then, they haven't just become an accessory; they've become an extension of my confidence and personal style. Let me tell you why:

It's no secret that feeling good about how you look translates to feeling good about yourself. And let me tell you, these Abe frames are confidence rocket fuel. Every time I catch my reflection, I see a man who means business, someone who exudes both style and substance. It's a subtle shift, but it makes all the difference.

The beauty of the Abe frames lies in their disarming simplicity. No unnecessary frills, no gaudy embellishments â€“ just classic elegance that enhances my persona without overpowering it. They seamlessly blend with my personal style, adding a touch of sophistication without ever feeling out of place.

 Finding glasses that fit well can feel like searching for a needle in a haystack. But the Abe frames? They're a match made in heaven. The weight is perfectly balanced, the shape flatters my face, and the fit is snug yet comfortable. It's like they were custom-designed for me!

These frames are more than just a way to correct my vision; they're an investment in myself. The quality is impeccable, and the Warby Parker experience, from browsing online to visiting the store, was exceptional. The entire journey was smooth, informative, and enjoyable.

It's been two months, and my love for these Abe frames hasn't wavered. They're a testament to the power of classic design, exceptional quality, and a perfect fit.

reviews.title: Not a great experience overall
reviews.review_text:
OK - background to my purchase. I bought glasses from Warby Parker while I was down in the USA (I live in Canada). A friend of mine had a good experience and said that I could avoid hassle and high costs through this retailer. 
I should also preface that every individual that helped me genuinely tried their best to help me through the process. However, it soon became a comedy of small errors that made the overall experience regretful. 

First off, I ordered two glasses and the shipping department sent one my glasses to a location in the USA - my friend was able to forward them but I was assured at the store that both pairs would reach me in Canada. Second, one of my pairs of glasses was a completely wrong size (wide) when the other pair was correct (medium). Third, when I got the wide pair and got them fitted at a different retailer in Canada, I was told by an optician that the combination of my thick lens and the moulded frame (not metal) was not recommended because even though they could be adjusted by bending the frame, they explained that, over time, the frame would 'bounce back' to its original shape - making them unwearable. 

The shipping experience was bad. I first contacted WP's support to inquire when I was getting into the fourth week without receiving my glasses - I was told it was still within their 'window' for delivery even though the tracking shown that it was in New York as 'processing' for 3 weeks. I had to contact them again when I realized they would not make their window, the second support person I contacted was much more helpful in figuring out that my medium glasses had gone astray in shipping. He corrected the issue by re-issuing my order (which took another 3 weeks to get to me). So, when it came to the wide pair, the glasses were obviously not going to work for me, I contacted support again to see what could be done. Due to the issue of me being in Canada, ordering from the USA, they recommended that I send the wide pair back for a refund. However, the shipping department (or a computer) did not take this into account and they sent me a return label as if I was in the USA (postage paid for the US Postal system). I had to contact them again to get a re-issue for my return label to send through a Canadian carrier.

As I said, the overall impression of Warby Parker was one in which their employees would try to help as best they could but I can honestly say that I won't consider going through them again. Unless, I do it locally (but that is obviously up to the cost they would charge for glasses in Canada - FYI, prescription glasses in Canada are burdensomely expensive compared to other markets). I know that my experience was unique but I sending this on with the hopes that things improve (and urge them to open a store in Calgary, Alberta).

reviews.title: A whole new simple, sophisticated look!
reviews.review_text:
It's been two months since I stepped into the Warby Parker store in New York and walked out with a life-changing pair of glasses: the Abe frames. Since then, they haven't just become an accessory; they've become an extension of my confidence and personal style. Let me tell you why:

It's no secret that feeling good about how you look translates to feeling good about yourself. And let me tell you, these Abe frames are confidence rocket fuel. Every time I catch my reflection, I see a man who means business, someone who exudes both style and substance. It's a subtle shift, but it makes all the difference.

The beauty of the Abe frames lies in their disarming simplicity. No unnecessary frills, no gaudy embellishments â€“ just classic elegance that enhances my persona without overpowering it. They seamlessly blend with my personal style, adding a touch of sophistication without ever feeling out of place.

 Finding glasses that fit well can feel like searching for a needle in a haystack. But the Abe frames? They're a match made in heaven. The weight is perfectly balanced, the shape flatters my face, and the fit is snug yet comfortable. It's like they were custom-designed for me!

These frames are more than just a way to correct my vision; they're an investment in myself. The quality is impeccable, and the Warby Parker experience, from browsing online to visiting the store, was exceptional. The entire journey was smooth, informative, and enjoyable.

It's been two months, and my love for these Abe frames hasn't wavered. They're a testament to the power of classic design, exceptional quality, and a perfect fit.

reviews.title: A Stellar Experience at Warby Parker: Exceptional
reviews.review_text:
I bought these frames about a month ago. I really like them. I'm also going to come back in a few weeks for the gold ones. Mary helped me with this. From the moment I stepped into the Warby Parker store, I was greeted by an atmosphere of warmth and professionalism. However, it was the exemplary service provided by the sales associate that truly made my experience unforgettable.

As someone with a narrower face, finding the perfect pair of glasses has always been a bit of a challenge. But the sales associate, whose name escapes me in my sheer delight, went above and beyond to ensure that I not only found frames that fit snugly but also resonated with my personality.

Her knowledge of the product line was impressive, and she expertly guided me through the selection process, considering not just the fit but also the style that best suited me. She patiently listened to my preferences and concerns, offering valuable insights and suggestions along the way.

What truly stood out was the genuine care and attention she showed throughout our interaction. It wasn't just about making a sale; it was about forging a connection and ensuring that I walked away completely satisfied. Their enthusiasm for their work was palpable, and it made the entire experience enjoyable and memorable.

Thanks to her guidance, I found a pair of narrow frames that not only complemented my face shape but also reflected my individuality. Such personalized service is rare in today's retail landscape, and the sales associate Mary deserves the highest praise for that.

In conclusion, my visit to Warby Parker was elevated to an exceptional level thanks to the incredible assistance provided by the sales associate. Her professionalism, expertise, and genuine kindness made all the difference, and I will undoubtedly be returning for all my eyewear needs in the future. If you're in search of the perfect pair of glasses, look no further than Warby Parker, where exceptional service by Mary awaits.

reviews.title: A Stellar Experience at Warby Parker: Exceptional
reviews.review_text:
I bought these frames about a month ago. I really like them. I'm also going to come back in a few weeks for the gold ones. Mary helped me with this. From the moment I stepped into the Warby Parker store, I was greeted by an atmosphere of warmth and professionalism. However, it was the exemplary service provided by the sales associate that truly made my experience unforgettable.

As someone with a narrower face, finding the perfect pair of glasses has always been a bit of a challenge. But the sales associate, whose name escapes me in my sheer delight, went above and beyond to ensure that I not only found frames that fit snugly but also resonated with my personality.

Her knowledge of the product line was impressive, and she expertly guided me through the selection process, considering not just the fit but also the style that best suited me. She patiently listened to my preferences and concerns, offering valuable insights and suggestions along the way.

What truly stood out was the genuine care and attention she showed throughout our interaction. It wasn't just about making a sale; it was about forging a connection and ensuring that I walked away completely satisfied. Their enthusiasm for their work was palpable, and it made the entire experience enjoyable and memorable.

Thanks to her guidance, I found a pair of narrow frames that not only complemented my face shape but also reflected my individuality. Such personalized service is rare in today's retail landscape, and the sales associate Mary deserves the highest praise for that.

In conclusion, my visit to Warby Parker was elevated to an exceptional level thanks to the incredible assistance provided by the sales associate. Her professionalism, expertise, and genuine kindness made all the difference, and I will undoubtedly be returning for all my eyewear needs in the future. If you're in search of the perfect pair of glasses, look no further than Warby Parker, where exceptional service by Mary awaits.

reviews.title: Excellent Quality Glasses and Service
reviews.review_text:
This is my first experience with online eyeglasses shopping and I love the Warby Parker experience. First of all, choosing lenses was enhanced by virtual try-on, which encouraged and taught me what shapes worked best for my face. Second, the free option to try on five frames at home allowed me to narrow down the choices even further.  Instructions that came with the frames gave me more information on how to judge which ones were best for my face.  I was able to decide between regular lenses in one pair, plus Rx sunglasses, or else clear lenses with transition darkening. I chose the latter.  Then, it was so easy to return the frames. Note, in my town, the USPS carriers wonâ€™t pick up parcels from homes, if they are not scheduled beforehand, but it was easy to drop off at the PO. 
Next step, ordering was easy, because I could send a photo of my prescription that I took with my phone. The order was completed with only one extra step because the PD, pupillary distance, was unclear on the copy of the Rx that I had. I could do that step with my phone, though. I was delighted that they were able to connect with my vision insurance immediately, even though my coverage was so new I didnâ€™t even have my ID card yet. I paid through PayPal, again easy. Finally, communication with them by email and online was clear, swift, easy, and professional. I heard by email each step of the way. Shipping was swift and tracking steps were announced. The glasses arrived safely and work very well. I bought elsewhere some polarized sunglasses that fit over these, because the transition ones darken only before getting in the car, but those other ones work even better over them inside the car glass. Iâ€™m having the best of all options for me this way, rather than separate eyeglasses and Rx sunglasses to carry around.  The glasses look good, as well. Learning to use the new Rx, putting the extra car shades over top didnâ€™t take long to get used to. I can see so well with these that Iâ€™ll use the Warby Parker service gladly in the future and will recommend it highly.

reviews.title: Think twice before purchasing
reviews.review_text:
Came in to purchase glasses for both my husband and me.   The personnel were very welcoming and knowledgeable.   They were even able to get me in for a quick eye exam For glasses and contacts.   The frame assortment was great!   I even got my glasses delivered to the store within a week.
Thatâ€™s the good.
Now the badâ€¦.
My husbands glasses never arrived.   The order was canceled.   I was notified they were ordered but never a notice that they were canceled.   When I picked up my glasses, I inquired about his status and thatâ€™s when I found out the order was cancelled.   A few days later, someone from the store called to ask who canceled the order and basically accused us of doing the canceling which was far from the truth.
On top of this, my trial pair of day contacts gave me a lot of issues.   I was unable to get the contacts out and had to sleep with them.   I woke up with tremendous eye pain.   And even though I contacted customer service the night before about my issue, I was told that there would be an optician who could help me out.   Being it was Fourth of July, I was relieved to hear this.   I went into the store and the optician was concerned that I might have scratched my eye and wasnâ€™t comfortable touching my eye.   So I had to pay $100 to go to an opticians office to get seen.
I never received a call from the Waterford store to follow up on me, nor have I received a call from their optometrist who had said they were going to order me contacts that might be a better fit.
So in conclusion, the store is nice, the personnel are friendly, the selection is good, back office is horrible and do not recommend optician services.   Next time I need a pair of glasses, going to try somewhere else.

reviews.title: Unwearable
reviews.review_text: I purchased a pair of prescription Braden sunglasses with progressive lenses.  I bought them because I liked the frames, I wanted a pair of sunglasses to leave at my summer home and, for prescription sunglasses, the price was very reasonable.  I brought them to my summer home and when I wore them for the first time, I noticed that there was quite a lot of glare bouncing off the inside of the lenses into my eyes from any light source behind or above me.  The glare was so intense that I simply couldn't wear the glasses, as the light seemed more intense with them than without them.  Unfortunately, at the time I noticed this, I was at my country home, 90 miles away from the nearest Warby Parker store and 1800 miles away from my home in Texas.  When I returned to my home in Texas, I brought the glasses back to a nearby Warby Parker store.  I told the salesperson that I thought that someone had forgotten to put an anti-glare coating on the back of the lenses.  He tried the glasses on and, based on the intense light reflected off the inside of the lenses from the display lights in the store, agreed with me and agreed to replace the lenses.  A few weeks later I was notified that new lenses in a new Braden frame had arrived at the store.  When I tried on the new pair of prescription Braden sunglasses, the same glare problem existed.  The glasses were simply unwearable.  At that time, another salesperson explained to me that Warby Parker does not put an anti-glare coating on the inside of its sunglass lenses!  The absence of such a coating completely defeats the purpose of sunglasses.   If that is true, and based upon my experience I have no reason to believe it's not, I strongly recommend not buying sunglasses from Warby Parker.  By the way, I was told that there is nothing further that Warby Parker can do for me and that no refund would be forthcoming.

reviews.review_text: I bought these a number of months ago and couldn't be happier.  Note:  These are medium size frames, and if you have a med/small face these are the perfect size.  Wide frames tend to look massive on my face.  I still have another Warby Parker from about 6 years ago - it's a rectangular shape, while the Waller is oval - but not overly oval - so perfect for what I wanted.   The try on program is great.  My old WP frames are still in excellent condition, other than some wear on the inside of the arm where the name and dimensions are slightly faded from moisture - they basically look new.  Yes they have fallen on the patio/tile, in the pool and no issues at all.  This speaks to the quality.  WP seems to hit the sweet spot for sunglasses in terms of price/quality at $95 for most.  Drugstore or some other online glasses range say $10-$40 but they either feel cheap or if you find one that seems decent initially out of the box - the quality isn't there and it will end up cracking, breaking, bending, screws coming loose etc. and it's not really worth getting.  The next price level for some of your various name brand sunglasses run from say $150-$225 significantly more than WP.  I would say WP can mostly stand shoulder to shoulder with them in terms of quality, design, look.  Try WP, make the comparisons yourself, you won't be disappointed.

reviews.title: Need to check frames before shipping

The frames were so off center (vertically and horizontally) that they were not comfortable to wear.  We had to go back to the store and get all three fitted.  I feel that a lot of time and frustration could have been saved if the frames had a basic check before they were shipped to us.  Do the frames lay flat on a table? Are the temples even on both sides?

I was a bit skeptical about an online company making my glasses but I honestly have zero complaints. I see great with them (it's a new prescription), I haven't had to make any adjustments, the frame is beautiful. Customer service was great too, I had to replace the prescription I initially gave them and they were very flexible and accommodating. I've bought the last 2 frames from Warby Parker (and had the glasses done by a brick-and-mortar) but I think I'll just have them do the whole thing again next time. reviews.title: Unwearable
reviews.review_text: I purchased a pair of prescription Braden sunglasses with progressive lenses.  I bought them because I liked the frames, I wanted a pair of sunglasses to leave at my summer home and, for prescription sunglasses, the price was very reasonable.  I brought them to my summer home and when I wore them for the first time, I noticed that there was quite a lot of glare bouncing off the inside of the lenses into my eyes from any light source behind or above me.  The glare was so intense that I simply couldn't wear the glasses, as the light seemed more intense with them than without them.  Unfortunately, at the time I noticed this, I was at my country home, 90 miles away from the nearest Warby Parker store and 1800 miles away from my home in Texas.  When I returned to my home in Texas, I brought the glasses back to a nearby Warby Parker store.  I told the salesperson that I thought that someone had forgotten to put an anti-glare coating on the back of the lenses.  He tried the glasses on and, based on the intense light reflected off the inside of the lenses from the display lights in the store, agreed with me and agreed to replace the lenses.  A few weeks later I was notified that new lenses in a new Braden frame had arrived at the store.  When I tried on the new pair of prescription Braden sunglasses, the same glare problem existed.  The glasses were simply unwearable.  At that time, another salesperson explained to me that Warby Parker does not put an anti-glare coating on the inside of its sunglass lenses!  The absence of such a coating completely defeats the purpose of sunglasses.   If that is true, and based upon my experience I have no reason to believe it's not, I strongly recommend not buying sunglasses from Warby Parker.  By the way, I was told that there is nothing further that Warby Parker can do for me and that no refund would be forthcoming.

I needed glasses for driving and the movies. The 2 I chose from the sunglasses rack for driving were perfect. 
I did chose the Whittier for inside help. All 3 frames I chose were well made. I am near sighted. As a 74 year old, I have worn glasses for many years. The vision was spot on. However, I believe the lenses are much thicker than I previously wore. Perhaps there in lays the savings.  To my issue: I would prefer a few more Narrow or Medium size frames for my petite face. I love the coverage for sunglasses, but would like more options. 
That said, I  am very happy with Warby Parker.
